# ── Per-drive key-wrapping (for portable USB decryption) ─────────────────────
# Files on external USB drives can optionally be encrypted with a per-drive
# Data Encryption Key (DEK) instead of the server master key above.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
#   1. Use the Admin API to set up key-wrapping on a drive:
#      POST /api/admin/storage/:id/setup-key  { "passphrase": "your-passphrase" }
#      This creates a key.blob file on the drive root.
#
#   2. After each server restart, unlock the drive before accessing files:
#      POST /api/admin/storage/:id/unlock  { "passphrase": "your-passphrase" }
#
#   3. To decrypt files on another machine (off-device), copy the entire drive
#      contents (including key.blob) and use the passphrase — see docs/key-wrapping.md.
#
# No extra environment variables are needed for per-drive key-wrapping.
# The passphrase is never stored on disk — only derived keys are used.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Server port
PORT=3001
